column5: Transcript
so the cartoon involves the roadrunner and the coyote
and the coyote is always trying to get the roadrunner
but the roadrunner’s too fast
so in the first scene it’s the coyote chasing the roadrunner
and he wants to eat him
he has like a knife and a fork
I guess yeah he wants you know to eat him
but the roadrunner outruns him
so he ends up getting really frustrated
and he like devises these different like plots
for how he’s gonna trap the roadrunner ?
and the first one he comes up with is that
he somehow attaches like a boxing glove on a spring to a boulder ?
and he rigs it up
so that when the roadrunner runs past he’ll release the boxing glove
and the spring will like punch him the roadrunner ?
but it doesn’t end it doesn’t work and whatever and ends up that
the coyote gets smooshed by the boulder
and he gets punched in the face
so the roadrunner gets away
so his second plot is that
he devises a tightrope ? between two cliffs
and he takes an anvil
and he walks out on the tightrope
so that the weight of the anvil will like lower the tightrope ?
so that when the roadrunner steps on it
when he’s on the road below
then he’ll like fling up in the air
but it doesn’t work
and the coyote gets thrown up in the air
and there’s no parachute in his little backpack ? to save him ?
so he like falls to the ground and I guess he dies or whatever
and then it switches to them chasing each other in like a mine field ?
but it’s underground ?
okay
so they’re wearing their little hats with the lights on it
so all you see is the little lights like chasing each other in the tunnels ?
and it finally ends with the coyote like lighting a match
and it lights up all the dynamite around him
that he doesn’t know that it’s there
and he ends up exploding the whole mine field
and that’s the end of the cartoon
